# Phase 3 — Monte Carlo What-If Simulation Engine

## Overview

Phase 3 adds a **parallelized discrete-event simulation layer** on top of the Phases 1 & 2 ML predictions. Where Phase 2 answers *"what will happen?"*, Phase 3 answers **"what happens if we change X?"** — quantifying operational risk under uncertainty through 1,000-run Monte Carlo simulations.

The engine models real Appian queue dynamics (Poisson arrivals, stochastic service times, agent capacity) using **SimPy**, drives parameters from Phase 2's LSTM/TFT forecasts and XGBoost breach probabilities, and produces statistically rigorous P10/P50/P90 risk distributions with full HTML reports.

---

