### `phase3_simulation/scenario_builder.py` [NEW — What-If Configurator]

**Purpose**: Defines what-if scenarios by specifying modifications to queue configurations.

#### `ScenarioParameter` (Enum)
```python
class ScenarioParameter(str, Enum):
    AGENT_COUNT      = "num_agents"        # staffing change
    ARRIVAL_RATE     = "arrival_rate"      # volume spike/drop
    SLA_HOURS        = "sla_hours"         # SLA tightening/relaxing
    SERVICE_RATE     = "service_rate"      # efficiency change
    COMPLEXITY_MIX   = "complexity_mix"   # shift to more HIGH complexity
```

#### `ScenarioModification` (dataclass)
```python
@dataclass
class ScenarioModification:
    queue_name: str          # "Payment Processing" or "ALL"
    parameter: ScenarioParameter
    mode: Literal["absolute", "delta", "multiplier"]
    value: float | dict      # e.g., -2 agents (delta), 1.5x arrival rate (multiplier)
```

#### `Scenario` (dataclass)
```python
@dataclass
class Scenario:
    name: str
    description: str
    modifications: list[ScenarioModification]

    def apply(self, base_configs: dict[str, QueueConfig]) -> dict[str, QueueConfig]:
        """Returns modified copy of queue configs with all mods applied."""
```

#### `ScenarioBuilder`
Factory class with **pre-built scenario library**:

| Scenario | What it tests |
|---|---|
| `baseline` | No changes — current staffing + volume |
| `agent_reduction_2` | Remove 2 agents from Payment Processing |
| `agent_reduction_all` | Remove 1 agent from every queue |
| `volume_spike_20pct` | 20% arrival rate increase across all queues |
| `volume_spike_50pct` | 50% arrival rate (Black Friday / quarter end) |
| `sla_tighten_compliance` | Compliance Check SLA: 4h → 2h |
| `sla_tighten_payment` | Payment Processing SLA: 2h → 1h |
| `agent_add_2_payment` | Add 2 agents to Payment Processing |
| `high_complexity_surge` | Shift complexity mix: 25% HIGH → 50% HIGH |
| `combined_worst_case` | Volume spike 30% + agent reduction 1 + SLA tightened |

```python
